        imageUrl: '/images/covers/impress.webp',
        status: 'Production',
        tier: 'production',
        githubUrl: 'https://github.com/menelekmakonnen/imPress.git',
        clientProblem: 'MMG Printing Press — a books-and-publications press handling approximately 4 long-cycle jobs per week — had no integrated system for job costing, accounting, or payroll. Pricing was inconsistent because there was no formula connecting paper costs, binding, printing runs, and margin into a per-book price. Financial records were maintained in basic spreadsheets with no double-entry discipline, making accurate P&L statements impossible. Payroll was calculated manually without accounting for staff absences, leading to overpayments and disputes.',
        solution: 'Deployed imPress as a complete press management system with real double-entry accounting at its core. The itemised book-job costing module calculates price-per-book with configurable margin based on paper, binding, ink, and labor inputs. The accounting engine implements a full Chart of Accounts, Journal, P&L, Balance Sheet, Trial Balance, and Debtors/Creditors tracking — all backed by an immutable double-entry journal. Absence-aware payroll automatically adjusts compensation based on attendance records. The role hierarchy spans GodMode (ICUNI), Owner/Admin, Accountant, Front Desk, and Production, with capability-based multi-role users who can hold permissions from multiple roles simultaneously. All rates are editable in Settings tables, and a built-in backend simulation enables offline demos.',
        businessImpact: 'Transformed MMG\'s financial operations from informal spreadsheets to proper double-entry accounting. The press can now generate accurate P&L statements, Balance Sheets, and Trial Balances at any time — a capability they never had before. Absence-aware payroll eliminated the overpayment disputes that were straining staff relations. Itemised job costing ensures every book is priced profitably with transparent margin calculations.',
        expertDeepDive: 'The double-entry accounting engine is the architectural centerpiece — every financial transaction (job payment, expense, payroll disbursement, supplier payment) creates balanced debit and credit journal entries in an append-only ledger. LockService wraps all financial writes to prevent concurrent mutations that could create imbalanced entries. The Chart of Accounts follows standard accounting structure (Assets, Liabilities, Equity, Revenue, Expenses) with press-specific sub-accounts. The capability-based access system differs from traditional RBAC: instead of a user having one role, they accumulate capabilities from multiple roles — a Front Desk user can also hold Accountant capabilities without needing a separate account. The built-in backend simulation implements the complete API surface with synthetic financial data, enabling full offline demonstrations without connecting to the production spreadsheet. All configurable rates (paper costs, binding costs, labor rates, tax rates) live in Settings tables that the Owner can modify without developer intervention.',
