        clientProblem: 'Ghana\'s trotro (minibus) transport system — the backbone of urban mobility for millions — operates with zero digital infrastructure. Routes are informal, schedules are non-existent, and passengers have no way to know when the next vehicle is arriving or which route to take for their destination. Previous attempts to digitize trotro have failed because they tried to impose ride-hailing models on a fundamentally different transport paradigm. The trotro system needs tools built for its own reality: fixed-ish routes, variable schedules, and cash-based fares.',
        solution: 'Built Trotro as the only project in the entire ICUNI portfolio that does not use Google Apps Script — instead leveraging Supabase for real-time database operations, authentication (SSR + JS client), and serverless functions. MapLibre GL provides open-source mapping with real-time vehicle positioning. The platform models trotro routes as flexible corridors rather than rigid paths, accommodating the reality of informal route variations. Built on Next.js 16 with React 19 and TypeScript, using UUID for entity identification.',
        businessImpact: 'Brings digital visibility to Ghana\'s most critical transport infrastructure. By modeling trotro operations as they actually work — rather than imposing a Western ride-hailing paradigm — the platform has a realistic path to adoption. The Supabase backend provides the real-time capabilities essential for live vehicle tracking without the infrastructure cost of managing WebSocket servers.',
        expertDeepDive: 'The architectural decision to use Supabase instead of Google Apps Script reflects the real-time requirements of transport tracking — GAS\'s request-response model cannot support live vehicle position updates at the frequency needed for useful mapping. Supabase\'s real-time subscriptions via PostgreSQL LISTEN/NOTIFY push vehicle position updates to connected clients instantly. MapLibre GL renders the map layer with custom tile sources optimized for Ghanaian road networks. Supabase SSR integration with Next.js 16 ensures server-side authentication for protected routes while the JS client handles real-time subscriptions on the frontend. UUID-based entity identification ensures unique vehicle and route tracking across the distributed system.',
