        solution: 'Deployed a corporate consulting website with a separate admin CMS called Studio for content management, enquiry tracking, audit logging, and governance. The Studio includes GodMode (full system access), impersonation (act as another user), and View-As (preview content from another role\'s perspective). The frontend is deliberately built as static HTML with no framework — hash-based routing handles navigation, and embedded fallback content ensures the site functions even when the GAS backend is unreachable. The backend comprises 13 GAS files: Auth.gs, Content.gs, Config.gs, Database.gs, Enquiries.gs, Router.gs, Setup.gs, and SeedPosts.gs. Dual deployment on Vercel (frontend) and GAS (backend) provides CDN-level performance with zero-cost API hosting.',
        businessImpact: 'Delivered a professional corporate presence with full content management capabilities at zero ongoing infrastructure cost. The static HTML + hash routing approach ensures the site loads instantly and works offline via embedded fallback content. The Studio\'s governance features (GodMode, impersonation, View-As) enable the consulting team to manage content collaboratively with full accountability through the audit log.',
        expertDeepDive: 'The no-framework frontend decision is architecturally significant — by using static HTML with hash-based routing (window.onhashchange), the site achieves near-instant load times and works entirely without JavaScript frameworks. Embedded fallback content means the site renders meaningful content even when the GAS backend is unreachable, using a progressive enhancement pattern where dynamic content replaces static placeholders when the API responds. The CORS challenge between Vercel (frontend) and GAS (backend) is solved via text/plain POST — GAS does not support standard CORS preflight requests, but text/plain content-type requests are classified as "simple requests" by browsers and bypass preflight entirely. The dual deployment strategy places the static frontend on Vercel\'s CDN for global edge delivery while keeping the API on GAS for zero-cost hosting. The audit log in Database.gs creates immutable records of every administrative action with timestamp, actor, action type, and affected content.',
